About the Series:
Detective Superintendent Peter Boyd is the leader of a police team which investigates 
unsolved murders using modern technology.
Starring  Trevor Eve, Sue Johnston and Wil Johnson.  

Episode 1 & 2 "Life Sentence"
The team are forced to enlist the help of a psychotic serial killer named Thomas Rice

Episode 3 & 4 "Deathwatch"
Boyd and the team take on the task of infiltrating the dark underworld of London's 
gangland crime families when small-time gangster Harry Newman makes a deathbed 
confession to twelve "unauthorised killings".

Episode 5 & 6 "Special Relationship"
When a petty criminal is acquitted of the murder of a prominent Home Office adviser 
and well known female activist, Boyd and his team struggle to find the identity 
of the real killer.

Episode 7 & 8 "Thin Air"
Twelve years after sixteen-year-old Joanna Gold famously disappeared in broad 
daylight on Hampstead Heath, the dress she was wearing is found in a lock-up 
garage owned by one of her old friends.
